In JUnitTestRunner#run method the following code is executed:

ByteArrayOutputStream errStrm = new ByteArrayOutputStream();
ByteArrayOutputStream outStrm = new ByteArrayOutputStream();

setupIOStreams(outStrm, errStrm);

these 2 output streams contain a byte buffer which is never cleared during the execution of the test. If you have a test or a suite of tests which perform a lot of console logging it will all add up to the content of the ByteArrayOutputStream byte[], which will increase in size when necessary, due to logging this happens.
This growing of this byte array will in the end lead to an OutOfMemoryError when the remaining amount of memory has become to small. 
So all loggers which log (in)directly using a ConsoleAppender add to this problem on logging on System.out.
